07389nam a22010575i 9783034614542DE-B159720211129102213.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211129t20122008sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830346145427 a10.11129/detail.97830346145422doi  a(DE-B1597)207912  a(OCoLC)979631802  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 4aNA2542.36 .E53 2012 7aARC0000002bisacsh04a720.47a720.4721 aHegger, Manfred, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aEnergy Manual :bSustainable Architecture /cManfred Hegger, Matthias Fuchs, Thomas Stark, Martin Zeumer. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2012] 4c©2008  a1 online resource (280 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aDETAIL Construction Manuals00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tPart A Positions -- tGlobal change -- tEnergy change -- tArchitecture and sustainability – a difficult relationship -- tDoing things right – on efficiency and sustainability -- tSolar Architecture -- tPlanning and building in life cycles -- tPart B Planning -- tFundamentals -- tUrban space and infrastructure -- tBuilding envelope -- tBuilding services -- tMaterials -- tStrategies -- tPart C Case studies -- tProject examples 1 to 20 200 – 257 -- tPart D Appendix -- tParameters -- tClimate data -- tLCA data -- tStatutory instruments, directives, standards -- tBibliography -- tPicture credits -- tSubject index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWhile the efficiency and sustainability offensive is in full swing in most sectors of the economy, in the construction sector it is still in its very beginnings – economically as well as ecologically. However, politicians and policymakers at the global, European, and national levels have begun to address this deficit and are seeking to correct it with legal requirements and laws like EnEV, building certifications, and competitions. Following the proven model of earlier manuals in the series, the Energy Manual presents a comprehensive look at the constructional parameters of energy efficiency and sustainability. It offers an advance look at the legal regulations being planned by the EU, and – as a tool ready for immediate use by architects, engineers, and designers in their daily work – it points the way toward the efficient and sustainable construction and operation of buildings. With its focus on the entire lifecycle of a building, it provides an integrated perspective – a necessary prerequisite for sustainable economic management.  aWährend die Effizienz- und Nachhaltigkeitsoffensive in den meisten Wirtschaftsbereichen in vollem Gang ist, steht das Bauen damit noch ganz am Anfang – ökonomisch wie ökologisch. Die Politik auf globaler, europäischer und nationaler Ebene nimmt sich dieses Defizits inzwischen zunehmend an und versucht es durch rechtliche Anforderungen und Gesetze wie EnEV, Gebäudezertifizierungen und Wettbewerbe wettzumachen. Der Energie Atlas gibt in der bewährten Form der Atlanten eine umfassende Darstellung der konstruktiven Parameter von Energieeffizienz und Nachhaltigkeit wieder. Er nimmt die von der EU geplanten gesetzlichen Regulierungen vorweg und weist als unmittelbar verwendbare Arbeitshilfe für die tägliche Arbeit von Architekten, Ingenieuren und Designern den Weg zu effizientem und nachhaltigem Bauen und Betreiben von Gebäuden. Mit seiner Orientierung am gesamten Lebenszyklus eines Gebäudes leistet er eine ganzheitliche Betrachtung – eine unverzichtbare Voraussetzung für nachhaltiges Wirtschaften.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aArchitecturexEnvironmental aspects. 0aSustainable architecture. 0aSustainable development. 4aElectricity. 4aEnergy concepts. 4aEnergy-efficient architecture. 4aEnergy. 4aLife cycle of materials. 4aSustainability. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh1 aHegger, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerzog, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaltenbrunner, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLenz, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuebkeman, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetzinka, Karl-Heinz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScheer, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStark, Thomas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aZeumer, Martin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062112908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ARTS AND ARCHITECTURE 2008z978311031899908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET KUNST UND ARCHITEKTUR 2008z9783110318890oZDB-23-DKA0 cprintz978376438764840uhttps://doi.org/10.11129/detail.978303461454240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783034614542423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783034614542/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-031899-9  E-BOOK PACKAGE ARTS AND ARCHITECTURE 2008b2008  a978-3-11-062112-9  DGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_C